stories.title: Zimbabwe's winning Streak
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Bangladesh, 5th ODI, Harare
stories.summary: Zimbabwe finally sealed the series 2-1, by beating Bangladesh by three wickets in the deciding match
stories.byline: The Wisden Verdict by John Ward at Harare

stories.title: Zimbabwe edge the series - but Mahmud almost the unlikely hero
stories.subTitle: Zimbabwe v Bangladesh, 5th ODI, Harare
stories.summary: A captain's innings from Heath Streak - and the nervousness which comes with not being used to winning from Bangladesh - enabled Zimbabwe to scrape to a three-wicket victory which had seemed highly unlikely when they slumped to 124 for 6 chasing 183
